  1. News & Announcements

  1. Celebrate Everett’s natural beauty with Rings & Roots

    Elementary students join Everett Parks & Community Services staff in annual events to preserve and beautify the city’s parks and open spaces. Rings & Roots consists of two events, held at some of Everett’s most beloved parks. Read on...

  2. New playground equipment coming to Deer Park

    Everett families and visitors should plan for a closure of the play area at Deer Park, 1300 55th St. SW, while crews upgrade playground equipment. The playground at Deer Park will close in late March to begin construction. Read on...

  3. Liz Vogeli appointed to National League of Cities’ Public Safety and Crime Prevention Committee

    The committee helps develop NLC’s federal policy positions on issues like crime prevention, corrections, substance abuse, municipal fire policy, juvenile justice, disaster preparedness, homeland security, domestic terrorism, court systems and gun control. Read on...
